      <hedline>
        <hl1>Clemens Reckless</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James English letter calls for dismissal of New York Yankees pitcher Roger Clemens for hitting Mets catcher Mike Piazzai</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>New Yorkers should give John Rocker the key to the city before they spend one more season with Roger Clemens. Dumb comments can be forgotten, but assassination attempts from 60 feet 6 inches can be career-ending and life-threatening. Bring that beanball over the plate instead and Piazza deposits it over a distant fence, as Clemens knows well.</p>
        <p>JAMES ENGLISH  Astoria, Queens</p>
      </block>
